<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Houston uses the buzz words "cop-killer bullets" and "assault rifles," neither 
of which are accurate descriptions -- they are are phrases manufactured by 
anti-gun organizations. The correct terminology is "armor-piercing ammunition," 
designed for use by police and military. 
</P>
<P>
Similarly, there is no such thing as an "assault rifle." If a 2x4 were used in 
the attack, would you call it an "assault board"? 
</P>
<P>
JON K. EVANS, Sherman Oaks 
