<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: RED ALL OVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Talking screenplay credits: Is Phil Alden Robinson -- writer-director of the 
weepy, uplifting "Field of Dreams" -- embarrassed by his script for 
"Relentless"? The potboiler, starring Judd Nelson as a deranged police academy 
reject-turned-serial killer, opened to mixed reviews Sept. 1, managing $3.2 
million in ticket sales its first weekend. 
</P>
<P>
But the name Phil Alden Robinson wasn't in the credits. 
</P>
<P>
A source tells us that Robinson -- who wrote the script several years ago, 
"before his career took another turn" -- won't allow the producing CineTel 
Films or the distributing New Line Cinema to connect his name to the movie. 
</P>
<P>
The credited screenwriter is "Jack T.D. Robinson." Sources tell us that's "Jack 
the Dog" -- Robinson's pooch. 
</P>
<P>
Calls to Robinson weren't returned. Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</TEXT>
