<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
FULLERTON FALLS TO USC IN WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Fullerton women's volleyball team lost to USC, 15-3, 15-13, 15-4, 
on Saturday in the Collegiate Premiere tournament at the Titan Gym. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton won its first three games of the tournament but lost Friday to San 
Diego State and Saturday to USC and did not place in the tournament. Fullerton 
now has a 4-3 record for the season. 
</P>
<P>
California defeated UC Santa Barbara 15-5, 13-5, 15-6, 8-15, 15-5, to win the 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
Outside hitter Rachel Wittliff, a freshman, led Fullerton with eight kills. 
Sabrina Dennis, who was named to the All-tournament team, and and Anne 
Witkowski each had five digs for the Titans. 
</P>
<P>
USC, 4-1 in tournament play, was led by outside hitter Lonise Norfleet and 
middle blocker Megan McCallister, who each had 12 kills. Stefanie Bodison had 
19 digs for the Trojans. 
</P>
<P>
At the Whittier College Invitational volleyball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
SCC def. Azusa Pacific 15-2, 15-10, 15-6 -- In the fifth-place match Heather 
Frewin had eight kills, Susan Rice had seven and Susan Dueker had six for 
Southern California College. 
</P>
<P>
Redlands def. SCC 10-15, 19-17, 15-13, 13-15, 15-10 -- In Saturday's early 
match, Frewin had 15 kills and Dueker had nine kills and five aces for Southern 
California College. 
</P>
<P>
At the Far West Soccer Invitational at Chapman College: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 1, Pacific Lutheran 0 -- In the third-place game, senior Keri Belo 
blocked three penalty kicks and Chapman scored its three to give Chapman the 
victory. Jeff Hudson, Jamie Wagner and Fabrizio Soto converted 12-yard penalty 
kicks for Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
Northeast Missouri State 1, Southern California College 0 -- Quinn Ross scored 
a header at 13:22 to give Northeastern Missouri State fifth place. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
Washington 1, Cal State Fullerton 0 -- Steve George's shot to tie the game with 
one left was saved by Washington's Rolf Noster as Fullerton (2-1) lost at 
Washington. 
</P>
<P>
At the Cal State Fullerton cross-country invitational: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton men's cross-country team finished third thanks to two 
impressive performances from freshman at Carbon Canyon Park in Brea. 
</P>
<P>
Tennessee finished first with 22 points, UCLA was second with 68 points and 
Fullerton had 74 points. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton freshman Steve Frisone, who graduated from Laguna Hills High School, 
finished eighth with a time of 25 minutes, eight seconds. Jose Brito, who 
graduated from Santa Ana Valley, finished 11th with a time of 25:06. 
</P>
<P>
In the women's division, Fullerton finished sixth but had a strong performance 
by freshman Beth Rosipajla, who graduated from El Dorado and finished seventh 
with a time of 18:35. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA won the division a score of 49, Arizona was second (56) and San Diego 
State (98) was third. UCLA was led by women's winner Kira Jorgensen who won 
with a time of 18:23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
