</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
POPE REPORTEDLY TO MEET WITH GORBACHEV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VATICAN CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pope John Paul II has agreed to meet with Soviet President Mikhail S. Gorbachev 
when the Kremlin leader visits Rome in November, the Italian news agency ANSA 
said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The Vatican has not yet officially announced the meeting, but ANSA quoted 
Vatican sources as expressing certainty the historic meeting will take place. 
Gorbachev is due to arrive in Italy on Nov. 25. 
</P>
</TEXT>
