<P>
CABRILLO BRIDGE CLOSED TO VEHICLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Balboa Park's Cabrillo Bridge will be closed to traffic until Oct. 15 while 
work is done on two bridge projects. As a result, access to the park will be 
limited to Park Boulevard and Presidents Way on the park's eastern side. 
</P>
<P>
The park's entrance at Balboa Drive and El Prado is undergoing a $150,000 face 
lift that will include repaving and landscaping improvements, according to Gary 
Stromberg, district manager of Balboa Park for the city's Park and Recreation 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
Interlocking brick-and-dirt beds will be added to the bridge's western side, 
Stromberg said. San Diego Trust &amp; Savings Bank is paying for the project as 
part of its 100th anniversary celebration. 
</P>
<P>
At the same time, storm drain reconstruction on the bridge's eastern side will 
be funded by the city. 
</P>
<P>
Construction work at both ends is expected to be completed before Oct. 15, 
Stromberg said. 
</P>
