<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE SOCCER; 
</P>
<P>
PIRI, BLUMKIN LIFT CS NORTHRIDGE OVER MASTER'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Northridge halfback Scott Piri scored on an assist from Bobby Reyes 
five minutes into the second half Saturday, and goalkeeper Jeff Blumkin 
recorded the Matadors' second consecutive shutout, stopping The Master's 
College, 1-0, before a crowd of 2,111 in a nonconference soccer match at 
Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
The teams combined for 56 fouls, four yellow cards, and two red cards. Master's 
(1-2) was down a player for 27 minutes in the second half because of a red card 
issued to Randy Whitfield, but the Matadors (2-0) could not capitalize. 
</P>
<P>
It was the second game in a row in which a CSUN player received a red card, 
this one going to Ed Burns. Blumkin was filling in for Mike Littman, who was 
red-carded for fighting in the Matadors' win over Cal State Los Angeles on 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Loyola Marymount 1, Occidental 0 -- The Tigers were unable to score for the 
second consecutive day and were eliminated from the Azusa Pacific tournament. 
Loyola broke a scoreless tie with 13 minutes to play. Goalie Lewis Tierney had 
eight saves for Occidental (0-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
