<HEADLINE>
<P>
WIERE GAINS TENNIS WILD-CARD SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steve Wiere of Calabasas advanced to the semifinals of the Volvo Tennis 
wild-card tournament Saturday by defeating Mitch Bridge of Huntington Beach, 
3-6, 7-6, 6-4, at the Racquet Centre of Universal City. 
</P>
<P>
Wiere, unseeded in the tournament, will play seventh-seeded Craig Johnson of 
Rolling Hills Estates today. Wiere beat Alex Reichel of Hacienda Heights in the 
first round and top-seeded Tim Pawsat of Santa Ana in the second. 
</P>
<P>
Tournament finalists will participate in the Volvo Tennis Los Angeles 
qualifying tournament at the Los Angeles Tennis Center, Sept. 16-17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
