<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNIVERSITY CITY ROLLS OVER SERRA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jerome Price caught three passes for 136 yards and two touchdowns to lead 
University City to a 23-6 victory over Serra Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Price caught scoring passes of 32 and 83 yards from Anthony Hill, and Kevin 
Hall kicked three field goals as University City took a 23-0 lead. Hill was 
eight for 19 for 228 yards. Robert Hamilton scored on a two-yard run for Serra. 
</P>
<P>
Castle Park 26, Christian 0 -- David Fernandes rushed seven times for 121 yards 
and scored three touchdowns to lead Castle Park at Christian. Castle Park 
quarterback Ernesto Diaz completed six of 11 passes for 95 yards and a 
touchdown. Christian turned the ball over four times on fumbles. 
</P>
<P>
Girls' volleyball 
</P>
<P>
Helix tournament -- Karrie Downey had eight kills and Nicki Cando added seven 
to lead Helix over San Marcos, 15-8, 15-9 in the championship match. Downey was 
voted the tournament's most valuable player. 
</P>
</TEXT>
