</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Miss Brio came from slightly off the pace to upset 1988 Kentucky Derby winner 
Winning Colors in the $111,800 Maskette Handicap Saturday at Belmont Park in 
Elmont, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
Winning Colors, the odds-on choice, tired abruptly after leading to the stretch 
and finished fourth in the field of five, creating unusually high show payoffs. 
</P>
<P>
Miss Brio, ridden by Jerry Bailey, won by 1 1/4 lengths and returned $8.80 to 
win, $5.20 to place and $14.00 to show. Proper Evidence paid $5.60 and $15.00, 
and Aptostar returned $12.80. 
