<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The New York chapter of the American Civil Liberties Union sent a letter to New 
York Yankees owner George Steinbrenner, asking him to explain the recent 
confiscation of negative banners at Yankee Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Norman Siegel, the ACLU's executive director, said that several 
anti-Steinbrenner banners -- including ones repeating the newly popular chant 
of "George Must Go" -- were recently confiscated by plain-clothes security men. 
</P>
<P>
"What we have here is a selective confiscation of banners," Siegel said. "And 
that concerns and disturbs us greatly. It's the kind of policy that should not 
be tolerated. It's entirely inappropriate behavior in a city-owned facility, 
and it represents an affront to the freedom of expression." 
</P>
</TEXT>
