<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAME HALTED 3 TIMES BY LIGHTNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WEST LAFAYETTE, Ind. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Purdue's 27-10 victory over Miami of Ohio was delayed three times for a total 
of 49 minutes while a series of thunderstorms passed over Ross-Ade Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
An unidentified 14-year-old girl was treated and released after lightning 
struck near her during halftime. She was was able to leave the stadium on her 
own, Purdue campus police said. 
</P>
<P>
ESPN, which was broadcasting the game, incorrectly reported that a second 
spectator had been struck by lightning, police said. The second person, who 
also was not identified, was taken to a local hospital for a physical problem 
unrelated to the weather, the Purdue sports information office said. 
</P>
