<DATE>
<P>
September 10, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Real Estate; Part 8; Page 8; Column 3; Real Estate Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
84 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREE CALIFORNIANS WIN FELLOWSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Alejandro Krell of UCLA and Mathew Anderson and Michael Smith-Heimer of UC 
Berkeley were among the 1989 winners of the Henry S. Miller Sr. and Jr. 
Fellowships awarded to California university graduate students. 
</P>
<P>
The awards are given by the Urban Land Institute to students following an 
interdisciplinary curriculum in real estate development. 
</P>
<P>
The Henry S. Miller Fellowship for Land Use and Development was made possible 
through a $100,000 grant to ULI from Good Gulfstream Foundation of Tampa, Fla. 
</P>
