<SECTION>
<P>
Real Estate; Part 8; Page 16; Column 1; Real Estate Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COMMERCIAL SCENE -- Burbank project -- NBC has applied for planning 
approval for a substantially redesigned NBC Plaza adjacent to the NBC 
headquarters at 3000 W. Alameda Ave., Burbank. The $200-million development 
will be a joint venture of NBC and Cushman Investment and Development. Ellerbe 
Becket is the architect of the 798,000-square-foot project bounded by Olive 
Avenue, California Street and the Ventura (134) Freeway. NBC Plaza will consist 
of two towers -- a 17-story and a 21-story one -- along with shops, restaurants 
and two acres of open space. There will be five levels of underground parking, 
instead of the four above-grade in the original 1987 design. Once approvals are 
obtained, construction is expected to begin late next year, with a 1993 
completion, according to an NBC spokesman. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
